                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1111 M Nielsen, Niels/4: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-04-17T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 17, 1933—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 17—5 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>334. My 324, April 13, 5 p.m. Following from American Consul General at Mukden:
                        <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 16, 9 a.m. Japanese military report that Nielsen was kidnapped by
                            bandits under Liu Ching-wen, a former magistrate and that he is believed
                            to be at a hamlet southwest of Siuyen.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
